Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are a promising solution to a sustainable energy future.
Titulo: High-Performance, Thermal Cycling Stable, Coking-Tolerant Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanostructured Electrodes

Sentencas: However, cell performance and stability remain a challenge.
Titulo: High-Performance, Thermal Cycling Stable, Coking-Tolerant Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanostructured Electrodes

Sentencas: Durable, nanostructured electrodes fabricated via a simple, cost-effective method are an effective way to address these problems.
Titulo: High-Performance, Thermal Cycling Stable, Coking-Tolerant Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanostructured Electrodes

Sentencas: In this work, both the nanostructured PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+delta (PBSCF) cathode and Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) anode are fabricated on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) backbone via solution infiltration.
Titulo: High-Performance, Thermal Cycling Stable, Coking-Tolerant Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanostructured Electrodes

Sentencas: Symmetrical cells with a configuration of PBSCF vertical bar YSZ vertical bar PBSCF show a low interfacial polarization resistance of 0.03 Omega cm(2) with minimal degradation at 700 degrees C for 600 h. Ni-SDC vertical bar YSZ vertical bar PBSCF single cells exhibit a peak power density of 0.62 W cm(-2) at 650 degrees C operated on H-2 with good thermal cycling stability for 110 h. Single cells also show excellent coking tolerance with stable operation on CH4 for over 120 h.
Titulo: High-Performance, Thermal Cycling Stable, Coking-Tolerant Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanostructured Electrodes

Sentencas: This work offers a promising pathway toward the development of high-performance and durable SOFCs to be powered by natural gas.
Titulo: High-Performance, Thermal Cycling Stable, Coking-Tolerant Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Nanostructured Electrodes
